138
00:07:16,102 --> 00:07:18,401
Fistful of pills like
that every morning?

139
00:07:24,210 --> 00:07:27,840
Yeah. And I see
that, um, you also...

140
00:07:28,581 --> 00:07:30,573
You lost your dad
a few years back?

141
00:07:32,719 --> 00:07:34,347
Yeah.

142
00:07:35,188 --> 00:07:37,521
Yeah, that's really
tough. I'm sorry.

143
00:07:40,794 --> 00:07:42,558
You know what, Leo?

144
00:07:44,197 --> 00:07:45,893
I want to try
something different.

145
00:07:46,266 --> 00:07:50,795
Instead of adding more medication
to your already impressive roster,

146
00:07:51,604 --> 00:07:53,402
why don't we try
this for a plan?

147
00:07:53,873 --> 00:07:57,275
Let's take you off all
of your medication.

148
00:08:04,417 --> 00:08:06,417
I just want to know how
much this is gonna cost me.

149
00:08:06,453 --> 00:08:07,944
I'm sorry, but I
can't tell you that.

150
00:08:08,054 --> 00:08:11,218
So I can compare prices on my Subaru
and not on my wife's double bypass?

151
00:08:11,291 --> 00:08:13,235
You know, it's funny,
Congress actually made it illegal

152
00:08:13,259 --> 00:08:15,057
for hospitals to
disclose prices to you,

153
00:08:15,128 --> 00:08:17,239
so it's the only industry in
America with a non-compete clause,

154
00:08:17,263 --> 00:08:19,789
but, hey, call your
congressperson. Resist!

155
00:08:21,735 --> 00:08:23,397
You're running late. - For what?

156
00:08:23,470 --> 00:08:25,302
For everything. Dora,
I'm educating patients.

157
00:08:25,405 --> 00:08:26,896
You're inciting riots.

158
