through Jozette's
heart is broken,

189
00:09:34,340 --> 00:09:37,538
and blood is backing up into her
lungs, which is why she can't breathe.

190
00:09:37,644 --> 00:09:40,580
But how could this
happen? Jozette is strong.

191
00:09:40,847 --> 00:09:43,146
She's an aid worker
for the people of Haiti.

192
00:09:43,216 --> 00:09:45,048
I have to get to Jean-Rabel.

193
00:09:45,351 --> 00:09:47,718
This week, a
mudslide hit our village.

194
00:09:47,821 --> 00:09:49,881
So many people have died.

195
00:09:50,557 --> 00:09:52,150
That might explain
what happened.

196
00:09:52,392 --> 00:09:54,361
You thinking takotsubo
syndrome? Yeah.

197
00:09:54,427 --> 00:09:55,486
That sounds bad.

198
00:09:55,562 --> 00:09:58,361
Another name for it is,
uh, broken heart syndrome.

199
00:09:58,565 --> 00:10:00,534
The mudslide may have
caused Jozette so much grief

200
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:02,728
that it actually made her
heart beat so hard that

201
00:10:03,169 --> 00:10:05,035
it tore the muscles
that hold it together.

202
00:10:05,105 --> 00:10:07,040
I hate to feel helpless.

203
00:10:07,107 --> 00:10:08,268
I'm sorry.

204
00:10:08,374 --> 00:10:11,071
Well, the good news is,
I can fix a broken heart.

205
00:10:11,711 --> 00:10:13,222
Now, we're gonna get
you prepped for surgery

206
00:10:13,246 --> 00:10:15,238
and get you home
as fast as we can.

207
00:10:16,616 --> 00:10:19,245
First may we perform a Gad Ko?

208
00:10:20,053 --> 00:10:23,182
I'm sorry, a what?
It's a protection ritual.

209
00:10:23,389 --> 00:10:26,018
We make a cut in
the skin, rub in herbs.

210
00:10:26,092 --> 00:10:27,770
Oh, no, that's... That's
out of the question.

211
00:10:27,794 --> 00:10:30,525
Any cuts to the skin can
introduce infection, so...

212
00:10:30,597 --> 00:10:34,557
Gad Ko attaches Lwa to me.
Protects me from accidents.

213
00:10:35,034 --> 00:10:38,198
Okay, look, Jozette, there
won't be any accidents, all right?

214
00:10:38,271 --> 00:10:40,968
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I have to prep for surgery.

215
00:10:48,748 --> 00:10:51,912
It's true. He used
to be energetic.

216
00:10:53,286 --> 00:10:54,777
Silly.

217
00:10:54,921 --> 00:10:58,722
But you can't just take him
off of all of his medications.

218
00:10:58,791 --> 00:11:00,760
Doesn't he need them?
Honestly, I don't know.

219
00:11:00,827 --> 00:11:02,090
I don't know what he needs.

220
00:11:02,162 --> 00:11:03,405
He's on so many
counterintuitive drugs,

221
00:11:03,429 --> 00:11:05,398
I can't see the real issue.

222
00:11:05,598 --> 00:11:07,260
I want to try
behavioral therapy.

223
00:11:07,767 --> 00:11:08,826
Talk therapy.

224
00:11:08,935 --> 00:11:10,267
He had, um,

225
00:11:11,738 --> 00:11:14,469
outbursts at school... Physical.

226
00:11:14,574 --> 00:11:16,975
And when the school psychiatrist
started him on the Zotepine,

227
00:11:17,076 --> 00:11:18,271
they completely stopped.

228
00:11:18,344 --> 00:11:20,813
That drug may have succeeded
in curbing your son's behavior,

229
00:11:20,914 --> 00:11:23,281
but it did nothing to address
the underlying issues.

230
00:11:23,349 --> 00:11:26,251
Zotepine also causes
lethargy, apathy.

231
00:11:26,319 --> 00:11:29,153
So when he was prescribed a
stimulant, that led to his sleep issues.

232
00:11:29,255 --> 00:11:30,848
And accelerated his weight gain,

233
00:11:30,957 --> 00:11:32,858
which developed
into Type 2 diabetes.

234
00:11:32,959 --> 00:11:34,136
That's why he's wetting the bed.

235
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:35,526
He has diabetes

236
00:11:35,828 --> 00:11:37,763
because of the
drugs that he's on.

237
00:11:39,165 --> 00:11:41,430
My God, I didn't...
I didn't know.

238
00:11:41,634 --> 00:11:43,234
I mean, they told me
that he needed them.

239
00:11:43,303 --> 00:11:44,613
I was just... I was
trying to help him.

240
00:11:44,637 --> 00:11:46,815
Of course, you were. That's
what we all would have done.

241
00:11:46,839 --> 00:11:48,000
Yes, absolutely.

242
00:11:48,474 --> 00:11:50,102
I'm sorry, I just...

243
00:11:50,810 --> 00:11:52,506
Let me pull him off the meds.

244
00:11:53,513 --> 00:11:56,108
You know, let me talk to him.
I really just want to talk to him.

245
00:12:01,287 --> 00:12:03,722
When was the last time
you saw your son smile?

246
00:12:10,630 --> 00:12:12,223
Dora, are you stalking me?

247
00:12:12,332 --> 00:12:14,677
It's definitely beginning to feel
that way, isn't it? Mmm-hmm.

